<p>You can specify a format string for the post date here. If you leave it blank or if you enter something invalid, it will use the Full Date Time Pattern.</p>
<p>Examples of valid patterns:</p>
<ul>
<li>MMMM dd, yyyy</li>
<li>MMM dd, yyyy</li>
<li>MM/dd/yyyy</li>
<li>dd/MM/yyyy</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/az4se3k1.aspx" target="_blank">Information about standard date/time format strings</a>.</p>
<p><a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/8kb3ddd4.aspx" target="_blank">Information about custom date/time format strings</a>.</p>